column3: Nature's finest. 100% pure. Unfiltered. Uncooked. Bee Natural Honey is unfiltered (strained) and bottled using minimum processing. This is done to maintain honey's natural color, flavor, and aroma. In addition, minimum processing retains honey's natural mix of enzymes, pollens, antioxidants, vitamins, minerals and antimicrobial properties. Pressure filtering and excessive heat can remove or destroy these beneficial properties. Bee Natural's mission is to retain each honey variety's unique characteristics. As a result, each particular honey may crystallize over time. This process is nature's own way of preservation and in no way affects honey quality. Upon crystallization, simply place the honey in hot water and let stand to reliquefy. Do not bring to a boil. See www.beenaturalhoney.com for all honey varieties. May include Limited Caribbean (DR). column1: YS Organic Bee Farms Honey, Raw
column3: World organic pioneer since 1995. 100% certified organic. USDA organic. Pioneer in organic bee farming. The pure frontier wilderness for organic bees fresh, clean, friendly, sustainable bio-eco system. As the world pioneer in certified organic bee farming, we have the true knowledge of quality differences of floral sources and regions. We have searched around the world to find the perfect isolated, safe, untouched areas where nature is abundant with wide variety of flowers that flourish in the undisturbed remote wilderness with clean air, soil, and water. Organic bees are in harmony and balance with nature to stay strong and healthy. Our organic honey is specially selected, harvested with extreme care, 100% pure, raw, unpasteurized and unfiltered fresh from the hives. Crystallization of honey naturally occurs and is essential, so we do not forcefully process to stop nature's way. The results produce a superior, energy packed honey with the highest possible levels of live enzymes, vitamins, minerals and antioxidants, known to be beneficial agents as a full spectrum functional whole food. Our organic commitment with lifetime dedication brings you nature's very best, a truly special and uncommonly high quality organic honey. As the seasons and floral sources change, so do the natural characteristics of honey. So enjoy nature's gift full of delicate flavors and rich, delightful tastes, unique to each floral season. US Grade A. Wholesome benefits as a functional food. Unpasteurized fresh raw state unfiltered. Pure, natural, healthy, safe, harvested with extreme care. Certified Organic By: OCIA International. column1: Weeks Works Honey Straws
Kodiak Cakes Flapjack and Waffle Mix, Power Cakes, Buttermilk, Protein Packed
column3: 100% whole grains. Add water only. Non-GMO, no preservatives. 14 g protein. 5 g fiber. Whole grains taste better. A portion of sales donated to grizzly bear and wildlife conservation. Whole Grain: 36 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. Made with freshly ground grains and no preservatives. Restoring the Flapjack Tradition: Long ago, flapjacks were the hearty mainstay of frontiersmen from the frigid Yukon to the High Sierra. These rugged mountain-men and homesteaders relied on a traditional flapjack that combined the rich, substantial taste of whole grain wheat with the light, mellow taste of whole grain oats. Those trailblazers had stumbled onto a superb nutritional combination. Their flapjacks contained a powerful source of carbohydrates, protein and fiber with very little fat. Today, few people know that the frontier flapjack and the ordinary pancake are not the same. At Baker Mills, we set out to restore the flapjack tradition with Kodiak Cakes. Our time-honored family recipe harkens back to another time and spans many generations. Kodiak Cakes were finally introduced to the world one summer day in 1982 when Penny Clark to mixed together the ingredients for her father's flapjack recipe to sell to eager friends and neighbors. She packed the mixes in brown paper lunch sacks, placed them in her eight-year-old son's red wagon, and sent him off into the neighborhood. In no time, he returned home with an empty wagon having sold every mix. From a little red wagon, to the best selling whole grain flapjack mix in the nation, Kodiak Cakes have come a long way. Yet the recipe continues to stay true to the old fashioned flapjack of years past because of our steadfast commitment to use only whole grains and all-natural ingredients. Kodiak Cakes are not for the faint-hearted, but for those of us who, like the old frontiersmen exploring and settling untamed wilderness, require nutrition, vitality, and taste. Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix can be used as a healthy alternative in recipes. Simply substitute 1 cup flour with 1 cup Kodiak Cakes Mix and omit salt and baking powder. For more recipes visit www.Kodiakcakes.com. Instagram: (at)kodiakcakes; (hashtag)kodiakcakes. Twitter: (at)kodiakcakes. Facebook: kodiakcakes. YouTube: kodiakcakes. Try Kodiak Cakes other great tasting, whole grain products. www.kodiakcakes.com. Non-GMO. Kodiak Cakes were finally introduced to the world one summer day in 1982 when Penny Clark to mixed together the ingredients for her father's flapjack recipe to sell to eager friends and neighbors. She packed the mixes in brown paper lunch sacks, placed them in her eight-year-old son's red wagon, and sent him off into the neighborhood. In no time, he returned home with an empty wagon having sold every mix. From a little red wagon, to the best selling whole grain flapjack mix in the nation, Kodiak Cakes have come a long way. Yet the recipe continues to stay true to the old fashioned flapjack of years past because of our steadfast commitment to use only whole grains and all-natural ingredients. Kodiak Cakes are not for the faint-hearted, but for those of us who, like the old frontiersmen exploring and settling untamed wilderness, require nutrition, vitality, and taste. Power Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix can be used as a healthy alternative in recipes. Simply substitute 1 cup flour with 1 cup Kodiak Cakes Mix and omit salt and baking powder. column3: Brighten your day with the sweet aroma of fluffy, piping hot pancakes and waffles. Our 10 Grain Pancake & Waffle Mix is full of wholesome goodness and irresistible flavor because we use only the finest all natural ingredients - stone-ground whole grain flours, aluminum-free leavening and pure sea salt. All natural. Whole Grain: 45 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. An employee-owned company. To your good health. - Bob Moore. Made with flax. Our product lien is diverse and extensive. For information and recipes, visit our website at www.bobsredmill.com. Diets rich in whole grain foods and other plant foods low in total fat, saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease and certain cancers. Dear friends, We would like to share with you the importance of including whole grain foods in your diet. A whole grain includes all three parts of the grain kernel: the bran, endosperm and germ. Whole grains have long been over-generalized as just a good source of dietary fiber, but they also contain important vitamins, minerals, and hundreds of unique phytochemicals. Recent scientific research has discovered that the benefits of eating whole grains come from the synergistic effects of the fiber, vitamins, minerals and phytochemicals - not just the individual components. They all work together to offer health benefits that are greater than the sum of the parts. Exactly how they work together is uncertain, but studies clearly show that including whole grains in your diet may reduce your risk of certain chronic diseases. Certain Cancers: Scientific evidence suggests that a diet including whole grains reduces the risks for some cancers, especially gastrointestinal cancers. Heart Disease: Antioxidants contained in whole grains may work with fiber and other compounds to reduce your overall risk of heart disease. So for your good health, start eating at least three servings of whole grain foods every day. My Bob's Red Mill 10 Grain Pancake & Waffle Mix is a delicious way to include them in your diet. It carries my highest endorsement. To your good health, - Bob Moore. Made in the USA.Show LessOur product lien is diverse and extensive. Long ago, flapjacks were the hearty mainstay of frontiersmen from the frigid Yukon to the High Sierra. Those trailblazers had stumbled onto a superb nutritional combination. Their flapjacks contained a powerful source of carbohydrates, protein and fiber with very little fat. In no time, he returned home with an empty wagon having sold every mix. From a little red wagon, to the best selling whole grain flapjack mix in the nation, Kodiak Cakes have come a long way. Yet the recipe continues to stay true to the old-fashioned flapjack of years past because of our steadfast commitment to use only whole grains and all-natural ingredients. Kodiak Cakes are not for the faint-hearted, but for those of us who, like the old frontiersmen exploring and settling untamed wildernesses, require nutrition, vitality, and taste. Kodiak Cakes Flapjack & Waffle Mix can be used as a healthy alternative in recipes. Simply substitute 1 cup flour with 1 cup Kodiak Cakes Mix and omit salt and baking powder. For more recipes visit www.kodiakcakes.com. Instagram at kodiakcakes, hashtag kodiakcakes. Twitter at kodiakcakes. Facebook kodiakcakes. YouTube kodiakcakes. www.kodiakcakes.com. Made with NON-GMO ingredients. Carton made from 100% recycled paper. Made in USA.

column1: Bobs Red Mill Gluten Free Pancake Mix
column3: An employee-owned company. Light fluffy. Great tasting. Wheat free. Dairy free. Naturally wholesome. You can see our quality. Our gluten free pancake mix makes up quickly and produces perfect, very light and fluffy pancakes everyone will enjoy. Use any kind of milk-soy, rice, almond, or cow-that is suitable for your diet. Add blueberries or bananas for pure pleasure. Casein free. Bob's Red Mill products labeled gluten-free are milled and blended in our dedicated gluten free packaging room, and batch tested in our dedicated gluten free quality control laboratory. We use an ELISA Gluten Assay test to confirm that a product is gluten free. Our product line is diverse and extensive. For information and recipes, visit our website at www.bobsredmill.com. Dear Friends, Since starting this company over thirty years ago, our mission has always been to offer the most diverse array of stone ground, whole grain products. About ten years ago, we noticed that some folks were exclusively buying gluten free grains like brown rice, sorghum and quinoa. Soon after that, we learned all about celiac disease and gluten intolerance and how serious they are to millions of people like you. Over the years we have introduced a variety of measures to ensure purity in our line of gluten free products that have become industry standard. We inspect all farm deliveries, use dedicated gluten free production facilities and employ batch testing in our quality control laboratory. knowing that we're providing safe and delicious gluten free foods that you and your family can trust makes it all worth the effort. To your good health, - Bob Moore. To learn more about our gluten free products and find superb recipes, visit www.bobsredmill.com/gluten-free. column3: Naturally flavored. First ingredient whole grain oats. Can help lower cholesterol (Three grams of soluble fiber daily from whole grain oat foods, like Honey Nut Cheerios cereal, in a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease. Honey Nut Cheerios cereal provides 0.75 grams per serving). Sweetened whole grain oat cereal with real honey & natural almond flavor. Simply made. Gluten free. Grown. Milled. Toasted. No artificial flavors. No artificial colors. Per 3/4 Cup Serving: 110 calories; 0 g sat fat (0% DV); 160 mg sodium (7% DV); 9 g sugars. See nutrition facts for as prepared information. First ingredient whole grain. A whole grain food is made by using all three parts of the grain. All General Mills Big G cereals contain more whole grain than any other single ingredient. Box Tops for Education. Same Cheerios, Simply Gluten Free: The real honey taste you love has always come with oats that are naturally gluten free. We're simply making sure they stay that way. It Starts with Family: When Phil, a member of the Cheerios team for over 50 years, found out his daughter-in-law couldn't eat gluten, he knew his team had to find a way to make sure every family, including his, could share breakfast together. Since oats are naturally gluten free, the only problem was finding a way to make sure they didn't get mixed up with anything else. What we put in: oats. What we sort out: wheat; rye; barley. The Journey from Field to Bowl: Most of the farmers who grow oats for Cheerios also grow wheat and barley, which aren't gluten free. Sometimes, those grains get mixed together in the field or on the farm, so, to make Cheerios gluten free, we had to separate them. It took a lot of late nights and hard work, but we finally discovered a way to sort the other grains out of our oats. Cheerios for Everyone: We know there are lots of families out there who don't want to let dietary restrictions get in the way of spending time together. Now that Honey Nut Cheerios are gluten free, more families than ever can sit down to share the taste of real honey and oats, and we couldn't be happier. After all, bringing families together around the breakfast table is exactly why we're here. Working with Nature: Cascadian Farm Roots: The story of Cascadian Farms starts over 40 years ago with Gene Kahn. Gene was an idealistic, 24-year-old graduate school dropout who wanted to make a difference in the world. Concerned about industrial farming's impact on our food and ecosystem, Gene was determined to help restore faith in food. So he founded a small, organic farm on a little stretch of land in beautiful Skagit Valley, Washington. That farm quickly grew and became a pioneer in the burgeoning organic food industry. Today, Cascadian Farm has grown well beyond the Home Farm, but Gene's mission continues: to bring you delicious, organic food you can believe in. Why We Go Organic: Why is organic so important to us? Simple. It's good for people and good for the environment. Organic farmers work with nature to build rich, healthy soil and preserve biodiversity and critical water resources. Organic farming also means crops are grown without the use of genetic engineering (GMOs) or synthetic pesticides and fertilizers. By eating organic, we not only limit our exposure to these synthetic chemicals but also respect and utilize nature's rich ecosystem. It's food just the way it should be. Visit Our Home Farm: We've outgrown our home farm in Skagit Valley, but you can still visit the place where it all started! Plan a trip and stop by our farm stand for a pint of our fresh, seasonal berries or homemade organic ice cream. If you aren't in the area, take an interactive virtual tour at CascadianFarm.com/farmtour. Open May-October. Cascadian Farm Home Farm, 55749 State Route 20, Rockport, WA 98283. Help us save the bees! Did You Know - Bees are responsible for the pollination of over two-thirds of the world's agriculture crops? Unfortunately, bee populations are declining at an alarming rate due to habitat loss, diseases, and pesticides. A world without pollinators would be a world without vital crops such as almonds, berries, and apples. What can you do to help? Plant native wildflowers in your yard. Choose organic. Visit Bee-Friendlier.com to enter the code below and we'll donate to help save bees (For every coded entered online, we will donate 25 cents to your choice of either Xerces Society or University of Minnesota Bee Lab. Maximum total donation of $1,000,000 based on online code entry and other consumer actions). Bee Friendlier by Cascadian Farm Organic. Yummy oven-roasted puffs of rice are a fat-free and cholesterol-free food. And they are an excellent source of vitamin C, thiamin, riboflavin, vitamins B6 and B12, niacin and folic acid. A good day starts with a good cereal. According to research, breakfast cereal eaters are better able to control their calories throughout the day. So, if you're watching your weight, start with a tasty, satisfying breakfast of cereal, milk and fruit. You'll rev up your metabolism by eating first thing. And by fueling up in the a.m., you'll be helping to curb those cravings throughout your busy day. Keep your workout going strong. Thiamin (vitamin B1) is a water-soluble B-complex vitamin essential for your body's metabolizing of carbohydrates into energy, helping support normal heart and nervous system function. During intense exercise, thiamin helps control lactic acid your muscles produce and convert it to glucose, which is then used for energy. Your body's individual requirement for thiamin is affected by the amount of carbohydrates you consume and energy you expend. Rise and Shine at Breakfast Time: Publix Corn Flakes are a good source of vitamins A, B6 and iron. This all-time breakfast favorite is also 99% fat-free, cholesterol-free food and an excellent source of folic acid and other essential nutrients. With no artificial flavors or colors, it's just plain good for you. Feel Good About Cereal for Breakfast: According to research, breakfast cereal eaters are better able to control their calories throughout the day. So if you're watching your weight, start with a tasty, satisfying breakfast of cereal, milk and fruit. You'll rev up your metabolism by eating first thing. And by fueling up in the a.m., you'll be helping to curb those cravings all day long. Get a Strong Start in the Morning: Your blood needs iron to help carry the oxygen your cells need to thrive. Your body keeps about 1/3 of its total iron in storage, ready to use as the need arises. Iron-fortified cereal may be a good way to help prevent iron deficiency, especially for teens, whose rapid growth and erratic eating habits make them prime candidates for anemia. Vitamin C can help your body absorb iron, so have a small glass of orange juice with breakfast for extra oomph. Publix Corn Flakes have a golden, crunchy goodness that's delicious on its own with milk or topped with your favorite fruit - from bananas to berries. Working with Nature: Organic Leader: Since our founding in 1972, Cascadian Farm has been recognized as a pioneer in organic farming. We were organic before organic was a trend, or even before it was certified by the USDA. Organic is who we've been, and it's who we are. Today our Cascadian Farm products still come from farming practices that work in harmony with nature and foster biodiversity and are grown without genetic engineering (GMOs) or synthetic pesticides. It's agriculture through nature, growing food just the way it should be. Cascadian Farm Profile Highlight: Name: Gene Kahn - Founder, 1972. Organic Commitment: Served on the USDA's National Organic Standard Board from 1992-1997. Why Organic: Organic farming methods have contributed to delivering healthy living, reducing toxic pesticide use, and restoring economic and environmental balance to our planet. Organic Pioneer: We're proud of the part Cascadian Farm has played in the organic movement for over 40 years and of the contribution we've made to a healthier environment. Visit Our Home Farm: We've outgrown our home farm in Skagit Valley, but you can still visit the place where it all started! Plan a trip and stop by our farm stand for a pint of our fresh, seasonal berries or homemade organic ice cream. If you aren't in the area, take an interactive virtual tour at CascadianFarm.com/farmtour. Open May-October. Cascadian Farm Home Farm, 55749 State Route 20 Rockport, WA 98283. Help Us Save the Bees! Did You Know: Bees are responsible for the pollination of over two-thirds of the world's agricultural crops? Unfortunately, bee populations are declining at an alarming rate due to habitat loss, diseases, and pesticides. A world without pollinators would be a world without vital crops such as almonds, berries, and apples. What Can You Do to Help? Plant native wildflowers in your yard. Choose organic. Visit Bee-Friendlier.com to enter the code below and we'll donate to help save bees (For every code entered online we will donate 25 cents to your choice of either Xerces Society or University of Minnesota Bee Lab. Maximum total donation of $1,000,000 based on online code entry and other consumer actions). 25 cents donation. Bee Friendlier by Cascadian Farm Organic. column3: Organic corn flakes, wheat flakes, whole grain oats and honey. Certified organic. Non-GMO (Organic products are not made with genetically engineered ingredients). No artificial colors or flavors. Bee Friendlier: Help us save the bees! See side of box to find out how. USDA organic. Visit our home farm. Skagit Valley, WA. Since 1972. 100% recycled paperboard. how2recycle.info. We welcome your questions or comments. 1-800-624-4123 (Mon-Fri 7:30-5:30 CT). Visit us at www.CascadianFarm.com. We're growing a better package. Inner bag made of up to 68% plant-based material. Box Tops for Education. Working with nature. Organic Leader: Since our founding in 1972, Cascadian Farm has been recognized as a pioneer in organic farming. We were organic before organic was a trend, or even before it was certified by the USDA. Organic is who we've been, and it's who we are. Today our Cascadian Farm products still come from farming practices that work in harmony with nature and foster biodiversity and are grown without genetic engineering (GMOs) or synthetic pesticides. It's agriculture through nature, growing food just the way it should be. Cascadian Farm Profile Highlight: Name: Gene Kahn Founder, 1972. Organic Commitment: Served on the USDA's National Organic Standard Board from 1992-1997. Why Organic: Organic farming methods have contributed to delivering healthy living, reducing toxic pesticide use, and restoring economic and environmental balance to our planet. Organic Pioneer: We're proud of the part Cascadian Farm has played in the organic movement for over 40 years and of the contribution we've made to a healthier environment. Visit our Home Farm: We've outgrown our Home Farm in Skagit Valley, but you can still visit the place where it all started! Plan a trip and stop by our farm stand for a pint of our fresh, seasonal berries or homemade ice cream. If you aren't in the area, take an interactive, virtual tour of the farm by visiting cascadianfarm.com/farmtour. Open May - October. Cascadian Home Farm 55749 State Route 20 Rockport, WA 98283. Help us save the bees! Did You Know - Bees are responsible for the pollination of over two-thirds of the world's agriculture crops? Unfortunately, bee populations are declining at an alarming rate due to habitat loss, diseases, and pesticides. A world without pollinators would be a world without vital crops such as almonds, berries, and apples. What can you do to help? Plant native wildflowers in your yard. Choose organic. Certified Organic: This product is certified organic by the Washington State Department of Agriculture in accordance with the organic standards of the US Department of Agriculture. This package is sold by weight, not by volume. You can be assured of proper weight even though some settling of contents normally occurs during shipment and handling. column3: Sweetened multigrain cereal. Naturally flavored with other natural flavors. Made with toasted flakes, honey, oat clusters & real strawberries. Provides a good source of 11 vitamins & minerals. Compare our product to Post Honey Bunches of Oats with Real Strawberries (Post Honey Bunches of Oats with Real Strawberries is a registered trademark of Post Foods, LLC. Publix is not affiliated with Post Foods, LLC). Nutrition for Your Sweet Spot: Fill your cereal bowl with healthy variety. Publix Strawberry & Oats is a delicious, sweetened multigrain cereal with toasted corn and wheat flakes, crunchy honey oat clusters, and real sliced strawberries. An excellent source of 9 vitamins and minerals, it's cholesterol-free and contains only 1 gram of fat per serving. A Good Day Starts with a Good Cereal: According to research, breakfast cereal eaters are better able to control their calories throughout the day. So, if you're watching your weight, start with a tasty, satisfying breakfast of cereal, milk, and fruit. You'll rev up your metabolism by eating first thing. And by fueling up in the a.m., you'll curb those cravings throughout your busy day. Smart Choices to Control Your Cholesterol: Are you one of the millions of Americans who need to watch their cholesterol? Eating right, maintaining a healthy weight, and exercising regularly are important. Having cereal as part of a balanced breakfast can be a great way to start eating better. Most of our cereals are low in fat and cereal is a cholesterol-free food, which makes it a good choice for your healthy lifestyle. Breakfast is the most important meal, so why shouldn't it be downright delicious? Treat yourself to crunchy wholesome grains and the tastes of honey and strawberries, and have a great day. publix.com. Diets rich in whole grain foods and other plant foods, and low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease. Go to http://postshreddedwheat.com for more details). An ingredients list that is so good, we have nothing to hide. Wouldn't it be great if it were easy to understand what is in your food? With Post Shredded Wheat, it's easy to be confident with your breakfast choice. It is made with nothing but goodness, so go ahead and enjoy a bowl. 100% Whole Grain Wheat and Wheat Bran: We make it easy to understand what is in your food - it's just the natural goodness of whole grain wheat and wheat bran. No Sugar (See nutrition information for calorie and sugar content. Not a low calorie food) or Salt Added: Our flavor comes from 100% whole grain wheat and wheat bran, nothing else. Never artificial fiber. Bite-Sized Health Tip: Nutritionists recommend eating at least 48 grams of whole grains a day. But instead of counting servings, enjoy one bowl of Post Shredded Wheat'n Bran. With 57 grams of whole grains per serving, you'll get 100% of what you need! Simple Things to Feel Good Each Day: Post Shredded Wheat is one of the simple things you can do to feel good each day. Here are a few other simple acts of goodness to tryout: Show appreciation to your spouse with a surprise breakfast in bed; Show thanks to your local neighborhood by picking up one piece of trash everyday; Thank a friend for her friendship by giving her the night off and babysitting her kids. The Biscuit of Benefits: Post Shredded Wheat'n Bran is made with 100% whole grain wheat and wheat bran, which are natural sources of fiber. It is also low in fat and cholesterol and sodium free. So what does this mean in terms of health benefits for you? They are so plentiful, the cereal could be renamed Biscuit of Benefits! Digestive Health: Diets rich in fiber have many benefits and are important for maintaining digestive health. Reduced Cancer Risk: Low fat diets rich in fiber-containing grain products, fruits and vegetables may reduce the risk of some types of cancer, a disease associated with many factors. And by fueling up in the a.m., you'll be helping to curb those cravings throughout your busy day. Dear Friends, You may notice some changes to the ingredient and nutrition details in our GoLean cereal and we want to share the full story behind them. First of all, we're proud to say that GoLean Original is now Non-GMO Project verified. In fact, ALL of our Kashi GoLean cereals are now Non-GMO Project verified. And we're working hard to have every Kashi product Non-GMO Project verified over the course of the year. Secondly, we're taking a different approach to harnessing the nutritional power of soy. It's called expeller pressing, and it's a method of simply squeezing the oils out of soybeans and using the protein that's left behind. While this approach is pretty simple, it's also a less efficient way to get protein, which resulted in a different serving size along with some differences in protein, fiber and sugar per serving. Finally, while you may find GoLean is a bit less sweet, we think you'll agree that it still tastes delicious and delivers an amazing combination of plant-based protein and fiber. We feel really positive about these changes and hope you do too. - Sincerely, The Kashi Team. We'd love to hear from you! If you'd like to know more or have any questions or feedback, please drop us a line at Kashi.com or on Facebook. Kashi eat positive. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the lightly honey'd gluten free flakes that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a gluten free breakfast with no artificial preservatives, color or flavors. Or maybe you were just looking for a lighter way to start your day? Whatever your reason for joining us on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you your family and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified Organic: Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because, really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen-not in a lab. Box Tops for Education. Working with Nature: Organic Farming & Pests: How we grow our food matters. That's why organic farmers use nature as an ally in their farming practices. When it comes to dealing with pests, organic farmers don't rely on synthetic pesticides. Rather, by fostering habitat for beneficial insects that prey on crop pests or by rotating crops to break crop pest cycles, organic farmers use the natural food web to help protect their crops. The result is a natural pest management system that is good for crops and good for the environment. It's agriculture through nature, bringing us food just the way it should be. Why We Go Organic: Why is organic so important to us? Simple. It's good for people and good for the environment. Organic farmers work with nature to build rich, healthy soil and preserve biodiversity and critical water resources. Organic farming also means crops are grown without the use of genetic engineering (GMOs) of synthetic pesticides and fertilizers. By eating organic, we not only limit our exposure to these synthetic chemicals but also respect and utilize nature's rich ecosystem. It's food just the way it should be. Visit Our Home Farm: We've outgrown our Home Farm in Skagit Valley, but you can still visit the place where it all started! Plan a trip and stop by our farm stand for a pint of our fresh, seasonal berries or homemade organic ice cream. If you aren't in the area, take an interactive, virtual tour of the farm by visiting CascadianFarm.com/farmtour. Open May-October Cascadian Farm Home Farm 55931 State Route 20 Rockport, WA 98283. Help us save the bees! Did You Know - Bees are responsible for the pollination of over two-thirds of the world's agriculture crops? Unfortunately, bee populations are declining at an alarming rate due to habitat loss, diseases, and pesticides. A world without pollinators would be a world without vital crops such as almonds, berries, and apples. What can you do to help? Plant native wildflowers in your yard. Choose organic. Starting your day off with a nutritious and satisfying breakfast is the smart way to jump start a healthy you. and with Kashi Go Lean Crisp! Toasted Berry Crumble it just got even tastier! Our cereal has twice the protein and fiber of the average of other cereals (Kashi Go Lean Crisp! cereal contains 8 g fiber and 9 g protein per serving; the average of 200 leading cereals contains 4 g fiber and 3 g protein per serving) - to help keep you feeling full longer (Go Lean products are designed to promote a feeling of fullness by increasing daily intake of protein and fiber. See nutrition information for details.)! And to make sure that your taste buds are just as satisfied, we combine a deliciously light and crispy whole grain cluster with a naturally sweet blend of cranberries and wild blueberries and then toasted them all to perfection. So add it all up and Kashi Go Lean Crisp! is sure to keep you going and satisfied all morning long! You'll feel great knowing that you won't have to give in to temptation because with the uniquely light, yet satisfyingly crisp clusters of Go Lean Crisp!, you've got the perfect breakfast, topping for yogurt or anytime snack to ward off those cravings - so enjoy! Our Go Lean Philosophy: At Kashi, we believe that everyone has the power to make positive, healthy lifestyle changes. But staying committed to healthy eating and exercise isn't easy. That's why we developed our Go Lean family of products, an assortment of delicious, convenient food options, to be an easy part of your commitment to a healthier, leaner you. What makes Go Lean effective? Each Go Lean product is designed with our unique combination of protein and fiber to help you stay satisfied. And they have the great taste and texture of real foods made with whole grains and all natural ingredients, so you look forward to enjoying them. Protein: Go Lean products provide a good source of protein from soy. Protein helps give you a lasting feeling of satisfaction and is essential for muscle development. Fiber: Each Go Lean product is high in fiber. Fiber helps you feel full longer and helps keep your digestive system running smoothly. Whole Grains: Go Lean products are made with whole grains that are packed with beneficial phytonutrients. Eating more whole grains and fiber-rich foods help manage hunger and is associated with a healthier body weight. To learn more about our Go Lean products, visit www.kashi.com/golean. Sunny Goodness in Every Bowl: Our bodies don't make any vitamin C; we must get our recommended daily value from outside sources. And if ever there was a versatile vitamin, this is it. Studies have shown it is helpful in preventing arteriosclerosis, heart disease, even arthritis. Enjoy a bowl of toasted, golden Publix Frosted Flakes. column1: Kashi Heart to Heart Cereal, Oat, Honey Toasted
column3: The seven whole grain company. 3 antioxidants (vitamins C and E and beta-carotene). American Heart Association certified - Meets criteria for heart-healthy food. Contents may settle, product sold by weight not volume. What does your heart mean to you? At Kashi, we believe that your heart is the essence of who you are. It is the engine of your body. A healthy heart enables you to do what you want. It allows you to be there for the people you love. So it's worth taking care of. That's why we created Heart to Heart foods to give you more tasty choices for your heart. Visit us at www.kashi.com/natural learning for inspiration for healthier eating and living. With Honey Toasted Heart to Heart cereal, you'll savor every spoonful knowing that it tastes good and it's good for you. Lightly sweet and crunchy, it's made from whole grain oats and our unique blend of Seven Whole Grains. Try our family of great tasting, Heart to Heart foods! Our family of heart healthy yummy products! From Our Heart to Yours: At Kashi, The Seven Whole Grain Company, we believe everyone has the power to make positive, healthy lifestyle changes. For over 25 years, it's been our mission to provide great tasting, all natural foods to help you live well. That's why we made our Heart to Heart foods with more heart healthy ingredients to: Help Support Healthy Cholesterol: Since high cholesterol is a major risk factor for heart disease, diets low in saturated fat and cholesterol that include 3 grams of soluble fiber per day from whole grain oats and oat bran may reduce the risk of heart disease. One serving of Heart to Heart cereal provides 1 gram of soluble oat fiber. This type of fiber dissolves in water to form a gel-like material and as it passes through the digestive system, it binds with cholesterol, removing it from your body. Good sources of soluble fiber include whole grains like oats, brown rice and barley, beans, peas, fruits and vegetables. Help Promote Healthy Blood Pressure: High blood pressure is another major risk factor for heart disease. Sodium is important to the body, but a high sodium diet is associated with hypertension. Diets low in sodium may reduce the risk of high blood pressure, a disease associated with many risk factors. That's why we made sure Heart to Heart cereal is a low sodium breakfast choice. More For You: Each serving of Heart to Heart cereal is high in antioxidant vitamins C and E. Plus, you'll get 100% daily value of heart healthy vitamins B6, B12 and folic acid. column3: Toasted whole wheat beery flakes & flaxseed. Since 1908. 9 g protein. Only 4 ingredients. Less than 1 g sugar. Omega-3 fatty acids from flaxseed. American Heart Association certified. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. We still make our cereal from the same simple 4-ingredient recipe created by Lafayette Uncle Sam Coltrin in 1908. We cook whole wheat berries sourced from the American Heartland with salt, whole flaxseed and a touch of barley malt to enhance the natural nutty flavor of the whole grains and steam them until soft. Next we roll them into flakes and oven-toast them to deliver the Uncle Sam Original Wheat Berry Flakes that have been enjoyed for over a century. Our traditional method preserves the nutritional value, shape and flavor of the whole grains while delivering 10 grams of fiber, 9 grams of protein and less than 1 gram of sugar per serving. A few ways our customers use Uncle Sam to get more whole grain fiber and protein in their diet are: Mix in with yogurt or ice cream; Sprinkle over hot cereals; In a bowl with fresh fruit and/or milk; Add to salads for a fiber/protein crunch. Thirty-some years ago, our founders set out on a mission for a healthier, more plant-powered way to fuel their active lifestyles - and just like that, Kashi was born. The adventure continues, and next they created Kashi GoLean - one of the first brands to bring plant-based protein to breakfast cereal. Today we're still passionate about new foods with plant-based nutrition. We understand that now more than ever active people like you want to get the most out of every bite, sip and slurp. So we developed our new Kashi GoLean Plant-Powdered Shakes for another option of nutrient-dense nourishment designed for your life in motion. column1: Grape Nuts Cereal, Flakes
column3: Power-packed nutrition. 47% of your day's whole grain. Whole Grain: 23 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. Per 3/4 Cup Serving: 110 calories; 0 g sat fat (0% DV); 135 mg sodium (6% DV); 4 g sugars; 3 g fiber (12% DV); iron (45% DV). What's your mountain? Sixty years ago Grape-Nuts was chosen to be part of man's first summit of Mount Everest. With power-packed nutrition, each nugget helped to provide concentrated, sustained energy that led to the ultimate conquest of the world's highest mountain. Since then, Grape-Nuts has given people around the world the energy they need to conquer their own mountains. From Everest to the everyday, Grape-Nuts has the power-packed nutrition you need to reach for the top! So, what's your mountain? This little flake has 3 big things going for it! Nutrition: Grape-Nuts Flakes cereal is loaded with whole grain. Just one serving provides 23 g, that's 47% of your day's whole grains (Nutritionists recommend at least 3 servings of whole grain foods each day [about 16g per serving or 48g per day])! Grape-Nuts Flakes are a natural source of fiber (3 g per serving), low in fat and cholesterol free. With all this, it's easy to see how Grape-Nuts Flakes can be an important part of your active, heart-healthy lifestyle (Diets rich in whole grain foods and low in saturated fat and cholesterol may help reduce the risk of heart disease)! The whole grains in Grape-Nuts Flakes are also a natural source of antioxidants. Grape-Nuts Flakes are also high in iron (45% DV/serving) and folic acid (50% DV/serving). Wow, there's a lot of nutrition in these little flakes! Crispy! Grape-Nuts Flakes have a unique texture all their own. These lightly crispy flakes are like no other! Taste: Made with natural whole grain wheat with barley, these tasty flakes have a slightly sweet, nutty flavor and deliciously light crunch. Enjoy them with milk and fresh fruit, sprinkled on a salad or mixed with low fat yogurt. For more ways to enjoy Grape-Nuts and Grape-Nuts Flakes, visit: www.postfoods.com. We're growing a better package. Inner bag made up to 68% plant-based material. Box Tops for Education. Working with Nature: Organic Farming & Pests: How we grow our food matters. That's why organic farmers use nature as an ally in their farming practices. When it comes to dealing with pests, organic farmers don't rely on synthetic pesticides. Rather, by fostering habitat for beneficial insects that prey on crop pests or by rotating crops to break crop pest cycles, organic farmers use the natural food web to help protect their crops. The result is a natural pest management system that is good for crops and good for the environment. It's agriculture through nature, bringing us food just the way it should be. Why We Go Organic: Why is organic so important to us? Simple. It's good for people and good for the environment. Organic farmers work with nature to build rich, healthy soil and preserve biodiversity and critical water resources. Organic farming also means crops are grown without the use of genetic engineering (GMOs) or synthetic pesticides and fertilizers. By eating organic, we not only limit our exposure to these synthetic chemicals by also respect and utilize nature's rich ecosystem. It's food just the way it should be. Visit our Home Farm: We've outgrown our Home Farm in Skagit Valley, but you can still visit the place where it all started! Plan a trip and stop by our farm stand for a pint of our fresh, seasonal berries or homemade organic ice cream. If you aren't in the area, take an interactive, virtual tour of the farm by visiting CascadianFarm.com/farmtour. Open May-October Cascadian Farm House Farm 55749 State Route 20 Rockport, WA 98283. A world without pollinators would be a world without vital crops such as almonds, berries, and apples. What can you do to help? Plant native wildflowers in your yard. Choose organic. Iron: A Strong Start is Important to Your Day: Your blood needs iron to help carry the oxygen your cells need to thrive. Your body keeps about 15% of its total iron in storage, ready to use as the need arises. Lack of iron in your diet can cause a deficiency, hindering overall health, suppressing immune system responses, and leading to weakness and fatigue. Feed Good About Cereal for Breakfast: According to research, breakfast cereal eaters are better able to control their calories throughout the day. So if you're watching your weight, start with a tasty, satisfying breakfast of cereal, milk, and fruit. You'll rev up your metabolism by eating first thing. USDA organic. 3 generations. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the crunchy clusters of whole-grain rolled oats that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a nutritious bowl of cereal when you came upon omega-rich pumpkin and flax seeds. Or, did you just have a craving for a tasty granola parfait? Whatever your reason for joining us on Nature's Path, we're glad you're here. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family, and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified Organic: Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non GMO: GMO stands for genetically modified organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project doesn't think so, and their verification ensures you our products are made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Whole Grains: Foods made from whole grains have all the essential parts and naturally-occurring nutrients of the entire grain seed, and the Whole Grain Stamp'll let you know how much you'll get per serving. Let us know how your journey's going, how we can make it better, or maybe even what you think of our new look. www.naturespath.com. Facebook: facebook.com/naturespath. Twitter: at naturespath. We'll see you on the path - how about breakfast, same time tomorrow? ALA omega 3's. Certified organic. Whole grain. High fiber. Contains 10 g of fat per 55 g serving. Growing up on an organic farm, I learned a lot about caring for the land and the importance of good stewardship. As my father Rupert used to say, Always leave the Earth better than you found it. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. Being a family-run, independent company, we've had the freedom to place people first and get behind the things we're passionate about. Things like tracking down exotic new ingredients and super foods, supporting family & organic farming, championing wildlife conservation and showing leadership in support for food banks and urban gardens. Things that matter, to us - and to you. - Arran Stephens, Founder & Garden-Keeper. EnviroBox: Less Package. More Sustainable. column3: Shredded wheat biscuits with cocoa & cinnamon. Made with transitional wheat. New! Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Transitional certified by QAI. Fair Trade certified cocoa. 6 g fiber. Contents may settle. Product sold by weight not volume. Newton Russell, looking out on his transitional fields in eastern Wyoming. This cereal is not organic. But hang on. That's the point. The truth is, less than 1% of farmland in the US is certified organic and transitioning conventional farmland to organic is difficult. Farmers like Newton often want to do it but they have to implement more costly methods for at least three years to become certified. And while that's good for all of us, it means farms don't see a return on their investment immediately, and they may be less motivated to make the change. So, let's do something about it. The Kashi Transitional Farms Initiative was created so together we can help farmers like Newton transition their farmland. During Newton's three-year conversion process, we're buying some of his transitional grains - which are certified by Quality Assurance International to ensure they are grown using sustainable practices that avoid genetically modified seed and synthetic pesticides or fertilizers. And we use them to make this cereal. Our hope is to convert more acreage every year - which is why our certified transitional cereals will always be made with transitional grains. The more we all become aware, the more farmers we can help to make a difference together. Thanks for joining us. Transitional Certified by QAI - Look for the mark of the movement. Dear Friends, At Van's, we believe that nutritious is delicious - that's why we made Cinnamon Heaven cereal. To create an absolutely new kind of gluten free snack, we went back to our California beachside roots for inspiration. It was there at the original Van's restaurant that we first dished up crazy whole grain and gluten free treats. That same passion for seriously wholesome, seriously tasty foods lives on at Van's today. Baked with oats, brown rice, millet, quinoa and amaranth, Cinnamon Heaven cereal delivers a full serving of whole grains. But the best part? The amazing taste and crunch your whole family will love. So dip your spoon into a sweet hint of cinnamon and say hello to a whole new, whole grain way to start your mornings. - Van's. Top 4 ways to eat our Van's cereal! The Old Standby (with Milk): Go bananas! Add some for a potassium boost. On-the-Run (Snacking): Keep in a resealable container and snack away. Go Nuts (Almond Milk): Use almond milk! Hodgson Mill Untoasted Wheat Germ is a delicious nutritious and versatile diet supplement! The germ is the embryo, the source of new life in the wheat kernel. It has a mellow, nutty flavor and it's brimming with important nutrients such as vitamin E, folic acid, magnesium and thiamine. Hodgson Mill gives you this bounty in a basic way - no added ingredients, nothing that diminishes the essential benefits. Enjoy the recipes on this package, or send for our recipe book (offer on inside flap). Nature didn't toast wheat germ neither do we! Hodgson Mill Untoasted Wheat Germ can be added to stews, chili, casseroles, gravies, vegetables, puddings, candies, stuffings, pancakes, waffles or pies. Also, sprinkle over dry or cooked cereals, sandwiches, and salads. A great addition for baked goods; add approx 1 tbsp of wheat germ for every 2 cups of flour. column1: Bobs Red Mill Muesli, Old Country Style
column3: An employee-owned company. To your good health. - Bob Moore. Hot or cold cereal. Whole grain. Wholesome. Nutritious. Whole Grain: 17 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. Resealable package. Dear friends, many years ago, my wife Charlee and I stayed at a beautiful bed and breakfast in the Scottish countryside. One morning, our hostess served us the most amazing cereal. It was full of rolled grains, nuts, seeds and dried fruit. This was my first contact with the traditional European cereal known as muesli. A quick bit of history: muesli was invented over a century ago by a Swiss doctor who was way ahead of his time when it came to understanding the health benefits of whole grains. He made all of his patients eat muesli every day, and they loved it! I enjoyed that muesli so much that I was inspired to make my very own version of this nutritious cereal. I started with a combination of five flavorful rolled grains - oats, wheat, barley, rye and triticale. Then I added sweet dates and raisins, crunchy sunflower seeds, almond slices and walnut pieces. Finally, for an extra boost of nutrition, I topped it off with a good handful of flaxseed meal. Voila! Bob's Red Mill Old Country Style Muesli was born. Whether you eat it hot, cold, or soaked in yogurt overnight (the traditional Swiss way), I just know you will enjoy this wholesome cereal. To your good health, - Bob Moore. Perfectly Simple Cereal: Our muesli is wonderfully tasty and nourishing! What makes this cereal so great? It's Perfectly Simple: whole grains provide nutritious fiber; dried fruit adds a touch of wholesome sweetness; nuts and seeds bring pleasant flavor and crunch. Still hungry? Was it the medley of ancient heirloom grains like Kamut khorasan wheat, spelt, barley, millet & quinoa that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a nutritious start to your day when you came upon this whole grain goodness. Or, were you simply looking for a breakfast that honored tradition? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family, and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Organic: Organic agriculture is a system of growing food in harmony with nature, avoiding toxic synthetic chemicals and genetically modified seeds. Our farmers use their intimate knowledge of the land to build up healthy soil and biodiversity. Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Whole Grains: Foods made from whole grains have all the essential parts and naturally occurring nutrients of the entire grain seed, and the Whole Grain Stamp tells you how much you'll get per serving. If you've got a story to share about our foods, we'd love to hear it. Organic brown rice served up twice with a touch of honey. What matters most is what's inside, the box: We believe pure ingredients taste better and are naturally nutritious, so that's what we use. We mix delicate crisps and tender puffs of US grown organic brown rice for two distinctive textures. Then we glaze the rice with a subtle blend of organic brown rice syrup and honey that sparkles with sweetness. Enjoy by the bowl or sprinkled over yogurt. What matters most is what's inside, you: We make our food with your digestive health in mind to keep you feeling good from the inside out. We proudly offer seven certified gluten free cereals. Gluten is the protein found in wheat. For people with celiac disease or gluten intolerance, the only treatment is a strict gluten free diet, which helps heal the small intestine, improving overall health. To learn more about celiac disease, please visit www.celiac.org. Food Allergies: Our cereals have no dairy, soy, peanuts or tree nuts in them. Visit www.attunefoods.com for further food allergy information. Since 1966, Erewhon has led the organic revolution and we remain passionately committed to providing the purest organic foods. Like many people today, you might actually find yourself wary of packaged foods. If what you eat is good, and pure, and true to its source, all else will follow. This philosophy shaped Erewhon organic cereals. The name Erewhon (Air-wahn) comes from a 19th century novel by Samuel Butler. Erewhon was a Utopia where each person was responsible for her/his own health, something we strive to make possible with Erewhon organic cereals. 100% whole grain. 21 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainCouncil.org. Certified gluten-free. Certified organic by Oregon Tilth. www.attunefoods.com. Using their talent for creating recipes and making delicious products, they created a complete line of granola bars, fruit & grain bars, fruit-flavored snacks and granola cereals-all providing a balance of great taste and nutrition. At Sunbelt, our philosophy is that it takes more than great taste and nutrition to have a winning recipe. We know that convenience can play a role in a balanced diet too. column1: Alpen Muesli, Original
column3: All natural. Excellent fiber source. Very low sodium. A pure, healthy way to start your day. Muesli recipes date back to late nineteenth century Switzerland, where they were first created to promote optimum nutrition and serve as the cornerstone for a healthy lifestyle and wholesome food plan. With these lofty goals in mind, Alpen was launched in the 1960's and it's been a family favorite ever since. Alpen Original is simple, versatile and satisfying. We blend benefit-rich whole grain rolled oats, barley and wheat flakes with toasted hazelnuts, sliced almonds, and raisins for a taste that's hearty and delicious. Alpen Original is bursting with whole grain fiber and supplies you with 6 grams of protein per serving. Enjoy Alpen hot or cold with milk or try it with fruit and yogurt for a healthy on-the-go snack. Heart Healthy: Soluble fiber from foods such as oats and barley, as part of a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease. A serving of Alpen Original supplies 0.76 grams of the 3 grams per day of soluble fiber from oats and barley necessary per day to have this effect. Dietary Features: Excellent source of fiber; 38 grams of whole grains; 79% of your daily whole grain needs; nonGMO; very low sodium; excellent source of phosphorus; lacto-ovo vegetarian; no artificial flavors, colors, or preservatives; 0 g trans fat per serving; no cholesterol; kosher. Since the 1960's, Alpen's timeless blend of simple whole grains, fruits, nuts and seeds has been a high-energy breakfast favorite. Free from artificial preservatives, flavors or colors. Alpen is a wonderful way to energize your day. Product of Canada.Show Lesss, barley and wheat flakes with toasted hazelnuts, sliced almonds, and raisins for a taste that's hearty and delicious. column1: Natures Path Organic Cereal, Flax Plus, Raisin Bran
column3: Excellent source of ALA omega-3 (Contains 0.7 g of ALA omega-3 per serving, which is 43% of the recommended daily value of 1.6 g). 3 generations. Per 55 g serving: 8 g fiber; 6 g protein; 14 g whole grains. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. USDA organic. This product is sold by weight, not by volume. You can be assured of proper weight even though some settling of contents normally occurs during shipment and handling. To maintain freshness, store in a cool, dry place. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the tasty trail of lightly-toasted multibran that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a source of good fats and fiber when you came upon delicious omega-rich flax flakes. Or, did you just have a craving for a big bowl of cereal? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you're here. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family, and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified organic. Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because, really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non-GMO. GMO stands for genetically modified organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Whole grains. Foods made from whole grains have all the essential parts and naturally occurring nutrients of the entire grain seed, and the Whole Grain stamp tells you how much you get per serving. Get in touch with us and let us know how your journey's going and how we can make it better, or learn more about things like organics, GMOs & gluten free. naturespath.com. Facebook/naturespath. Twitter at naturespath. We'll see you on the path - how about breakfast, same time tomorrow? Certified organic. Whole grains. High fiber. Growing up on an organic farm, I learned a lot about caring for the land and the importance of good stewardship. As my father Rupert used to say, always leave the Earth better than you found it. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. Being a family-run, independent company, we've had the freedom to place people first and get behind the things we're passionate about. Things like tracking down exotic new ingredients and super foods, supporting family & organic farming, championing wildlife conservation and showing leadership in support for food banks and urban gardens. Things that matter, to us - and to you. Arran Stephens. Founder & garden-keeper. EnviroBox. Less package. More sustainable. column3: We believe what matters most is what's inside. Same great product. Since 1966. 100% whole grain cereal. USDA organic. Organic. Gluten free. Less than 1 g of sugar. Low fat. Simple ingredients. Simply made. People have gathered around the table for years to share food and stories, feeding the stomach and the spirit. At Attune Foods, we make food we want to eat with you in mind. We believe pure ingredients taste better and are naturally nutritious, so that's what we use. We ourselves are label readers and know it's important for the ingredients listed to make sense to you. We believe in the wisdom imparted by our grandparents that balance and mindful eating are part of a healthy lifestyle. Attune Foods commits to bringing you food that helps you feel good and that you can feel good about eating with your family. So that's us. If you've got a story to share about our foods, we'd love to hear it. Non-GMO project verified. Certified gluten-free. 100% whole grain: 28 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. Certified organic by Oregon Tilth. America's favorite organic crispy brown rice cereal. What matters most is what's inside, the box: We believe pure ingredients taste better and are naturally nutritious, so that's what we use. We take whole grains of US grown organic brown rice and blend them with gluten free organic brown rice syrup and sea salt to enhance the natural flavor of the whole grain. Then, we cook the rice and puff it to its crispy best. Enjoy by the bowl, sprinkled over yogurt or in your favorite treat recipe. What matters most is what's inside, you: We make our food with your digestive health in mind to keep you feeling good from the inside out. We proudly offer seven certified gluten free cereals. What is gluten? Gluten is the protein found in wheat (including semolina, spelt, kamut, einkorn and farro), barley, rye and triticale. Why gluten free? For people with celiac disease or gluten intolerance, the only treatment is a strict gluten free diet, which helps heal the small intestine, improving overall health. Food Allergies: Our cereals have no dairy, soy, peanuts or tree nuts in them. Since 1966, Erewhon has led the organic revolution and we remain passionately committed to providing the purest organic foods. Like many people today, you might actually find yourself wary of packaged foods. If what you eat is good, and pure, and true to its source, all else will follow. This philosophy shaped Erewhon organic cereals. The name Erewhon (Air-wahn) comes from a 19th century novel by Samuel Butler. You can be assured of proper weight even though some settling of contents normally occurs during shipment and handling. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the lightly sweetened gluten free flakes that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a nutritious start to your day without any additives, preservatives or coloring. Or were you simply looking for a tasty crunch to start your day? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you your family and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Organic: Organic agriculture is a system of growing food in harmony with Nature, avoiding toxic synthetic chemicals and genetically modified seeds. Our farmers use their intimate knowledge of the land to build up healthy soil and biodiversity. Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Certified gluten free. Veganic: Good Food Grown Safely: Our veganic farmers use smart growing techniques such as cover crops and alternating plant varieties over time to build nutrients in the soil. No pesticides, no herbicides, and no chance for contaminants to enter the food chain via application of biosolids or any other non-plant fertilizer to fields. Veganic farming is a step beyond organic - a step toward greater purity, greater health benefits and a safer food supply. Sprouting Unwraps Nature's Gifts: When a grain begins to sprout, extraordinary things happen. The plant begins to make a wealth of proteins, vitamins, minerals and antioxidants available - for its own future in the sun, it thinks, but really for you. The result is improved digestibility, bioavailability of nutrients, and a surprising burst of flavor. Every ingredient has a story. Puffin Trivia: Did you know that puffins can sit on your breakfast table? Puffins are usually 10 inches tall, which is about the height of a quart of milk. Puffins can see underwater to catch fish. They have special nictitating membrane eye covers which they can close while swimming. These function like goggles and even have a clear patch in the center to help them focus. Puffins can drink salt water and separate the salty brine in their salt glands, located over their eyes. The extra salt dribbles out of their nostrils. Puffin eggs are creamy white, sometimes with a lilac-colored pattern. To watch Puffins on the loafing ledge or in a chick burrow via live HD cams, visit our friends at explore.org. www.explore.org/puffins. Project Puffin: Barbara's is a longtime supporter of project puffin which, through the Audubon society, has restored puffins to their former habitat of Eastern Egg Rock off the rugged coast of Maine. for more information on how project puffin enables puffin colonies to flourish. Bio-Familia was established in 1954 in Sachseln, a quaint village nestled in the beautiful Swiss countryside. We are known worldwide as the pioneer maker of traditional Swiss Muesli, but few know of our early role in supporting natural farming techniques that respect the environment. Since 1958, Bio-Familia has been using organically grown cereals and fruits in our products. A close relationship with Dr. Hans Muller, the pioneer of organic cultivation in Switzerland, made Bio-Familia one of the first companies to discover the benefit of growing grains that replenish and maintain healthy soil while eliminating toxic chemicals. Tanks to this experience and know-how, Bio-Familia manufactures naturally grown cereal products that deliver outstanding taste and quality. Familia is proud to continue our tradition of bringing you wholesome and unique cereals grown in harmony and balance with the land. 100% of nature's best in every bowl. Pictured above are my wife, Margrith, and myself Fritz Dahler. My family pioneered Swiss organic farming in 1947, and were the first supplier of organic cereal of the Bio-Familia AG. This is our home and our farm. We are second generation Dahler family, and we continue to this day to proudly work the land on our family farm we call Dahler Hof, located in Noflen, Switzerland. Try our tasty recipes. Find out about our sustainability efforts, our history or order online www.bio-familia.com. www.bio-familia.com. Packed in a protective environment. column1: Food for Life Ezekiel 4:9 Cereal, Golden Flax
column3: Sprouted grain crunchy cereal. 6 g dietary fiber. 8 g protein. See side panel for more information. Less than 1 g sugar. Whole Grain: 47 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. As described in the Holy Scriptures: Take also unto thee wheat and barley and beans and lentils and millet and spelt and put them in one vessel and made bread of it. - Ezekiel 4:9. Certified organic grains. The live grain difference! Did You Know? Food For Life Ezekiel 4:9 sprouted grain crunchy cereals are made from sprouted organic live grains, legumes, and seeds, and contain absolutely no flour. Sprouting is the only way to release all of the vital nutrients stored in whole grains. We add just the right amount of water to healthy, whole, organically grown grains to unlock dormant food energy and maximize nutrition and flavor. Beneficial enzymes are activated which cause the grains to sprout and become a living food. The enzymatic action increases valuable nutrients and also causes a natural change that promotes a more efficient assimilation of protein and carbohydrates. Our exclusive slow baking technique helps preserve valuable nutrients and retain important natural fiber and bran. Your body and taste buds will know the difference. The natural whole grain goodness and energy source of crunchy Ezekiel 4:9 cereal is a great way to start the day off right. Ezekiel 4:9 cereal can be enjoyed as a hot or cold breakfast cereal. Top with fresh fruit for a healthy snack anytime, such as after a workout or in the evening. Hot Cereal Lovers combine Ezekiel 4:9 cereal with a rice milk, soy milk or coconut juice, and heat. Our cereals contain no refined sugar, preservatives, artificial colors or flavors, no shortening and no cholesterol. You can see, taste, and smell the live grain difference of our crunchy cereals. The Original 100% Flourless Complete Protein: Ezekiel 4:9 Sprouted Grain Crunchy Cereal is inspired by the Holy Scripture verse: Take also unto thee wheat and barley and beans and lentils and millet and spelt and put them in one vessel and make bread of it. This biblical cereal is truly the staff of life. The Nutrition Truth: We discovered when these six grains and legumes are sprouted and combined, an amazing thing happens. A complete protein is created that closely parallels the protein found in milk and eggs. In fact, the protein quality is so high, that it is 84.3% as efficient as the highest recognized source of protein, containing all 9 essential amino acids. Plus, there are 18 amino acids present in this unique cereal from all-vegetable sources! Yeast-free. No added oil. No artificial flavors. USDA organic. Certified organic by QAI. Questions/Comments: Call us at 1-(800) 797-5090 (M-Th 8-5, F 8-2 PST). www.foodforlife.com. This package is sold by weight, not volume. Contents may settle during shipping. Please recycle. column1: Natures Path 3 Generations Organic Cereal, Mesa Sunrise
column3: Corn, flax, quinoa & amaranth. Gluten free. Good source of ALA omega-3 (Contains 0.3 g of ALA Omega-3 per serving, which is 18% of the recommended daily value of 1.6 g). Wheat free. Certified gluten-free. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. USDA organic. This product is sold by weight. not by volume. You can be assured of proper weight even though some settling of contents normally occurs during shipment and handling. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the trail of toasted gluten-free flakes or the sprinkling of ALA omega rich flax seeds that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a nutritious bowl of cereal when you came upon this unique blend of quinoa, corn, and nutty amaranth. Or, maybe you just wanted a breakfast inspired by the traditional foods of the Mesa Verde Mountains. Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family, and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified Organic: Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because, really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Gluten Free: Sit back, relax, and enjoy, knowing this cereal has been given the ok by the world's leading gluten free certification program (in addition to many other delicious gluten free cereals and snacks made in the Nature's Path kitchen). Let us know how your journey's going, how we can make it better, or maybe even what you think of our new look. www.naturespath.com. facebook.com/naturespath. Twitter at naturespath. We'll see you on the path - how about breakfast, same time tomorrow? Gluten free. Wheat free. Certified organic. Growing up on an organic farm, I learned a lot about caring for the land and the importance of good stewardship. As my father Rupert used to say, Always leave the Earth better than you found it. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. Being a family-run, independent company, we've had the freedom to place people first and get behind the things we're passionate about. Things like tracking down exotic new ingredients and super foods, supporting family & organic farming, championing wildlife conservation and showing leadership in support for food banks and urban gardens. Things that matter, to us - and to you. - Arran Stephens Founder & Garden-Keeper. EnviroBox: Less package. More sustainable. We're committed to being as sustainable as possible, which is why we are always trying to make our packaging as small as we can. That said, you may have noticed this box is a bit smaller than it used to be - with the same amount of cereal. Good source of ALA omega-3 (Contains 0.3 g of ALA Omega-3 per serving, which is 18% of the recommended daily value of 1.6 g). Vegan. column1: Hodgson Mill Wheat Bran, Unprocessed
column3: Millers bran. Premium quality. Since 1882. Add to cereals, casseroles, cookies, breads, yogurt & more! See recipes on back of box! High in fiber. Good source of niacin & iron. Fat free. Sugar free. Cholesterol free. Sodium free. A heart healthy addition to breads, muffins, cereals, cookies & much more! Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Sealed inner pouch. Reclosable top. See inside flap for additional wheat bran recipes offer! Did you know? Hodgson Mill Unprocessed Wheat Bran - in the most natural form, right off the mill - comes from the outer protective coat of the wheat kernel. It is one of the best available sources of insoluble fiber. Wheat Bran is an easy and inexpensive way to add needed fiber, or roughage, to your family's diet. Wheat Bran's insoluble fiber is essential for helping to keep the digestive system working properly. Low fat diets rich in fiber - containing grain products, fruits and vegetables may reduce the risk of some types of cancer, a disease associated with many factors. Certified Organic Grains. Did you know? Food For Life Ezekiel 4:9 Sprouted Grain Crunchy Cereals are made from sprouted organic live grains, legumes, and seeds, and contain absolutely no flour. Sprouting is the only way to release all of the vital nutrients stored in whole grains. We add just the right amount of water to healthy, whole, organically grown grains to unlock dormant food energy and maximize nutrition and flavor. Beneficial enzymes are activated which cause the grains to sprout and become a living food. The enzymatic action increases valuable nutrients and also causes a natural change that promotes a more efficient assimilation of protein and carbohydrates. Our exclusive slow baking technique helps preserve valuable nutrients and retain important natural fiber and bran. Your body and taste buds will know the difference. The natural whole grain goodness and energy source of crunchy Ezekiel 4:9 cereal is a great way to start the day off right. Ezekiel 4:9 cereal can be enjoyed as a hot or cold breakfast cereal. Top with fresh fruit for a healthy snack anytime, such as after a workout or in the evening. Hot Cereal Lovers combine Ezekiel 4:9 cereal with a rice milk, soy milk or coconut juice, and heat. Our cereals contain no refined sugar, preservatives, artificial colors or flavors, no shortening and no cholesterol. You can see, taste, and smell the live grain difference. column1: Kashi Cereal, 7 Whole Grain Nuggets
column3: The seven whole grain company. Savor every hearty bite of whole grain & sesame goodness in our crunchy Nuggets, for an all natural, healthy start to a good day. Seven whole grains are better than one! 51 g whole grains 7 g fiber. Join Us Online: www.kashi.com/join; coupons; recipes; newsletters; connect with others. Contents may settle. Product sold by weight not volume. For over 25 years, we've been dedicated to making all natural, high quality foods with positive nutrition and great taste. Our mission to help people enjoy healthier foods was sparked by our passion for whole grain nutrition. After mixing grains and seeds for months, we chose the unique blend known as Kashi Seven Whole Grains & Sesame which continues to inspire nearly every food we make. Just as it's important to have a variety of fruits and vegetables in your diet, it is beneficial to eat a variety of whole grains. That's why we have seven instead of one. Together, Kashi's seven whole grains and sesame seeds provide plant protein, fiber and an assortment of vitamins, minerals and phytonutrients not found in most single-grain foods. Research also shows that eating whole grains is associated with a healthier body mass index, lower risk of heart disease and staying more satisfied throughout the morning. Whole grains truly are one of nature's premier superfoods that help you fed your best. Our seven whole grains also provide a variety of colors, textures, shapes and flavors for pure eating enjoyment. With tasty, real food, we believe eating healthy also makes you happy! Learn more about Kashi Seven Whole Grains & Sesame: Buckwheat: Hearty in flavor, this seed-like fruit is a good source of fiber. Triticale: Natural cross between durum whet and rye, with higher protein than both. Rye: Resilient staple grain with a distinctive earthy flavor. Hard Red Wheat: Hardy grain with nutty taste often used as bread flour. Barley: Smooth, malty flavor and a great source of soluble fiber. Oats: Naturally sweet and prized as a great source of soluble fiber. Brown Rice: Has a delicate flavor and five times the fiber of white rice. Sesame: Widely popular and tasty seeds, rich in minerals & healthful polyunsaturated fats. Kashi 7 whole grains are pure, smart and sustaining, full of flavors and textures to enjoy. Working at Kashi has helped me see how important living a natural lifestyle can be to overall health. Simple foods can be some of the most wonderful treats, like this tasty Tabbouleh salad Tina-Operations. Have something to share? We'd love to hear from you! Visit us at www.kashi.com. We are known worldwide as the pioneer maker of traditional Swiss Muesli but few know of our early role in supporting natural farming techniques that respect the environment. Since 1958 Bio-Familia has been using organically grown cereals and fruits in its products. A close relationship with the pioneer of organic cultivation in Switzerland, Dr. Hans Muller, made Bio-Familia one of the first companies to discover the benefit of growing grains that replenish and maintain healthy solid while eliminating toxic chemicals. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the crunchy, tasty little morsels that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a very high source of oatbran and psyllium fiber? Or were you just looking for a crunchy topping on your yogurt, baking or salad? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified Organic: Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because, really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that the food you're buying is made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Heart Healthy: Diets low in saturated fat and cholesterol and rich in fruits, vegetables and grain products that contain some types of dietary fiber, particularly soluble fiber, may reduce the risk of heart disease, a disease associated with many factors. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. Being a family-run, independent company, we've had the freedom to place people first and get behind the things we're passionate about. Things like tracking down exotic new ingredients and superfoods, supporting family & organic farming, championing wildlife conservation and showing leadership in support for food banks and urban gardens.
