USDA organic. Arrowhead Mills - America's organic company. Arrowhead Mills has been a pioneer and leader in organic cereals, baking mixes, grains, and nut butters since our founding more than 50 years ago in 1960. Our organically grown ingredients are handled and distributed based on a strict set of standards. We purchase our wholesome ingredients directly from local suppliers whenever possible, thereby reducing the miles your food travels to market. We emphasize environmental responsibility by maintaining sustainable farming practices. We do not use potentially harmful synthetic pesticides and herbicides on our organically grown ingredients. We take decisive steps to shrink our carbon footprint and conserve our planet including post-consumer, recyclable packaging along with water based inks. The Wholesome Benefits of Whole Grain Spelt: Arrowhead Mills Organic Spelt Flakes were developed based on the principle that the best tasting foods can also be wholesome and nutritious too. Hardier than many grains, Spelt was one of the original grains grown by early farmers. With 25 g of whole grains per serving, a good source of fiber and more protein than common wheat, it is a cereal you can feel good about enjoying every morning. Go ahead, try 'em and see for yourself how good whole grains can taste! Arrowhead Mills provides the ultimate in whole grain goodness with an array of breakfast products to choose from and get your day started right. Whether you prefer puffs, flakes, shredded wheat, pancakes & waffles, or hot cereal Arrowhead Mills offers unparalleled all-natural nutrition, quality and taste. For latest product information visit us at www.arrowheadmills.com. Our Partner: Jimmy Wedel. Wedel Farms. column1: One Degree Organic Foods Cereal, Veganic Sprouted Ancient Maize Flakes
column3: Every ingredient has a story. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. USDA organic. NSF: Certified gluten-free. Veganic: Find out more on the back! Sprouted maize. Sweetened with coconut palm sugar. Gluten free. Ingredient Story: Meet some good natured grains with simple stories to tell. Track it! M6E2FS. OneDegreeOrganics.com. Scan the code to discover the source of each ingredient in this cereal. Of good conscience. Delicious! Traceable! Think inside the box. Scan the QR code to trace every single ingredient in this box - down to the last grain. Ancient Maize: Diego Rivara Alberti, Buenos Aires Argentina. Buckwheat: Nicole Davis Estevan, Saskatchwean Canada. Coconut Palm Sugar: Ben Ripple Ubud, Bali Indonesia. 100% Transparency = Power + Peace of Mind: Taste is the first of your senses that will celebrate a spoonful of sprouted ancient maize sweetened with coconut palm sugar. Add to that the incredible thrill of knowing the story of your food. We give you the power to trace every ingredient back to the organic farm where it grew - and to the farmer who stands behind its purity. See each harvest. Hear each family's stories and dreams. Feel an exhilarating bond with the land. Now your senses have really come alive. Meet the actual farmer who grew the crop, and discover the real story of your food. OneDegreeOrganics.com. Veganic: Good Food Grown Safely: Our veganic farmers use smart growing techniques such as cover crops and alternating plant varieties over time to build nutrients in the soil. No pesticides, no herbicides, and no chance for contaminants to enter the food chain via application of biosolids or any other non-plant fertilizer to fields. Veganic farming is a step beyond organic - a step toward greater purity, greater health benefits and a safer food supply. Sprouting Unwraps Nature's Gifts: When a grain begins to sprout, extraordinary things happen. The plant begins to make a wealth of proteins, vitamins, minerals and antioxidants available. The result is improved digestibility, bioavailability of nutrients, and a surprising burst of flavor. Together with the pure goodness of maize and buckwheat, you've now set the table for a breakfast the way nature imagined it, and the generations once enjoyed it. A New Dimension in Healthy Food: Transparency: You have the power to trace every ingredient. Accountability: Our farmers are proud of their harvests, and never anonymous. Certified Organic: Free of harmful pesticides and herbicides. Veganic: Cultivated without animal based fertilizers - a new higher standard. Non-GMO: We've never once thought about improving nature's designs! Sprouted Grains: Better digestibility and bioavailability of nutrients. Coconut Palm Sugar: Naturally low glycemic index sweetener with an indescribable taste! Gluten-Free Ancient Heritage Grains: Maize is the corn our grandparents knew, before corporate labs decided to hybridize and genetically modify grains. The maize and amaranth in this box are nature's original designs. Plus, our recipe is completely gluten-free. It's the kind of purity and honesty that's been missing from breakfast. This product is third-party certified organic by Quality Assurance International (QAI). Certified gluten-free by NSF. Certified Organic: Quality Assurance International. column1: Natures Path Organic Cereal, Sunrise Crunchy Maple
column3: Corn, rice, flax, quinoa, buckwheat & amaranth. Gluten free selections. 3 generations. Gluten free. 12 g whole grain. Wheat free. Low fat. Certified gluten-free. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. USDA organic. This product is sold by weight, not by volume. You can be assured of proper weight even though some settling of contents normally occurs during shipment and handling. We're So Happy Our Paths Have Crossed: Was it the crunchy medley of whole-grain flakes, quinoa puffs and crispies that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a nutritious gluten free snack when you came upon this unique blend of protein-rich quinoa corn and nutty amaranth. Or did you just have a craving for maple syrup? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. And if you want to find more foods that are good for you, your family and the planet, here are the signs to look for. Certified Organic: Unlike natural label claims, certified organic products are guaranteed to have been grown without chemical herbicides and pesticides, and there are never synthetic preservatives or additives. Because really, who wants any of that for breakfast? Non-GMO: GMO stands for Genetically Modified Organisms. Doesn't sound too tasty, does it? The Non-GMO Project agrees, and their verification assures you that foods are made in a kitchen - not in a lab. Gluten Free: Sit back, relax, and enjoy, knowing this cereal has been given the OK by the world's leading gluten-free certification program (in addition to many other delicious gluten free cereals and snacks made in the Nature's Path kitchen). Let us know how you're journey's going, how we can make it better, or maybe even what you think of our new look. www.naturespath.com. facebook.com/naturespath. Twitter at naturespath. We'll see you on the path - how about breakfast, same time tomorrow? Whole grain. Certified organic. Growing up on an organic farm, I learned a lot about caring for the land and the importance of good stewardship. As my father Rupert used to say, 'always leave the earth better than you found it'. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. Being a family-run, independent company, we've had the freedom to place people first and get behind the things we're passionate about. Things like tracking down exotic new ingredients and super foods, supporting family & organic farming, championing wildlife conservation and showing leadership in support for food banks and urban gardens. Things that matter, to us - and to you - Arran Stephens, founder & garden-keeper. EnviroBox. Less package. More sustainable. We're committed to being as sustainable as possible, which is why we are always trying to make our packaging as small as we can. That said, you may have noticed this box is a bit smaller than it used to be - with the same amount of cereal. Vegan. column3: Superfood breakfast cereal. 6 g protein (per 30 g serving), 4 g fiber (per 30 g serving), 2.5 g ALA omega-3s (per 30 g serving). USDA organic. Non GMO Project verified. Certified gluten-free. Gluten and wheat free; vegan; excellent source of ALA omega-3 (Contains 2.5 g of ALA omega 3 per serving, which is 156% of the recommended daily value of 1.6 g); no added salt; no added sugar; good source of fiber (Contains 7 g of fat per 30 g serving). Looking for a tasty and healthy alternative to your regular breakfast cereal? Qi'a (pronounced kee-ah) is our new superfood cereal made with Chia, Hemp and Buckwheat. This power trio of seeds is full of plant-based protein, fiber and ALA omegas. Boost your nutrition with only 2 tbsp of cereal and feel the energy from these powerful, functional, and nutritious super seeds. (Why so little? Chia expands up to 16x it's volume to fill you up). If you are looking for a zero sugar option, our Original blend is the perfect choice. Enjoy as a breakfast cereal, hot or cold; or add to yogurt, smoothies, oatmeal, or salads for an added nutritional boost. History of Quinoa: Quinoa (keen-wa), known to Bolivians as the Mother Grain, is now being heralded as the Supergrain of the Future. Ancient Harvest has worked with local, indigenous farming communities for over 30 years to offer delicious authentic foods you can trust. Our ancient grains descend from farms that span the entire length of the Bolivian Altiplano (high plains) at the base of the Andes Mountains. Not only do our products deliver a taste your whole family will love, but they are always gluten free, organic, non-GMO and delicious. Now you can enjoy the goodness of quinoa in an instant! Ready in 90 seconds, Quinoa Flakes make a smooth and delicious hot cereal. Eat them plain or spice them up with your favorite toppings. Quinoa Flakes are not only for breakfast. Substitute a portion of Quinoa Flakes for flour in your favorite cookie recipe, include some in your smoothie for added nutrients and texture, or use them in place of bread crumbs to create the perfect gluten free coating on chicken tenders or fish. Taste the Ancient Harvest difference! Learn more at ancientharvest.com. Certified Organic by Quality Assurance International (QAI). Please recycle. Country of Origin: Bolivia.Show LessMountains. column3: Pride of the mill. Made with flax. Contains flaxseed. You can see our quality! Bob's Red Mill 7 Grain Cereal is a creamy porridge carefully milled from a unique blend of flavorful whole grains. Top this incredible cereal with dried fruit and nuts for a delicious start to the day that will keep you satisfied all morning. A good source of fiber and packed with nutrients, this favorite of the mill contains wheat, rye, triticale, oats, oat bran, barley, brown rice and flaxseed. All natural. Whole Grain: 37 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. An employee-owned company. To your good health. - Bob Moore. Write for a brochure or product list: Bob's Red Mill Natural Foods, Inc. 13521 SE Pheasant Court Milwaukie, Oregon 97222. Dear friends, We would like to share with you the importance of including whole grain foods in your diet. A whole grain includes all three parts of the grain kernel: the bran, endosperm and germ. Whole grains have long been over-generalized as just a good source of dietary fiber, but they also contain important vitamins, minerals, and hundreds of unique phytochemicals. Recent scientific research has discovered that the benefits of eating whole grains come from the synergistic efforts of the fiber, vitamins, minerals and phyto-chemicals - not just the individual components. They all work together to offer health benefits that are greater than the sum of the parts. Exactly how they work together is uncertain, but studies clearly show that including whole grains in your diet may reduce your risk of certain chronic disease. Certain Caners: Scientific evidence suggests that a diet including whole grains reduces the risks for some cancers, especially gastrointestinal cancers. Heart Disease: Antioxidants contained in whole grains may work with fiber and other compounds to reduce your overall risk of heart disease. So for your good health, start eating at least three servings of whole grain foods every day. My Bob's Red Mill 7 Grain Hot Cereal is a delicious way to include them in your diet. It carries my highest endorsement. Come visit us right now at www.bobsredmill.com. To your good health, Bob Moore. Our product line is diverse and extensive. For information and recipes, visit our website at www.bobsredmill.com. Our product line is diverse and extensive. For information and recipes, visit our website at www.bobsredmill.com. Made in the USA.Show Lessain: 37 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily. WholeGrainsCouncil.org. An employee-owned company. To your good health. - Bob Moore. Health Valley Organic Oat Bran Flakes Baked Multigrain Cereal provides smart, delicious nutrition. Whether you enjoy them for breakfast or a snack, our deliciously crunchy and satisfying cereal is ideal for a healthy lifestyle. We are committed to providing you with foods that contain wholesome, organically grown ingredients that are good for you and the environment. In Health Valley Organic Oat Bran Flakes Baked Multigrain Cereal, there are: no potentially harmful pesticides; no highly processed ingredients like high fructose corn syrup; no artificial flavors, colors or preservatives. Our nutrition scorecard ensures that this cereal is: low in sodium; low in fat; lower in sugar than previous formulation; an excellent source of fiber; an excellent source of 6 B vitamins. All the benefits of fiber, and great taste, too. These hearty, delicious flakes have 29 g of whole grains in every serving. Health Valley Organic Oat Bran Flakes Baked Multigrain Cereal is an excellent source of fiber (5 grams) and has the benefits of 1.1 grams heart healthy soluble fiber (beta glucan) from oats and oat bran. Soluble fiber from oats and oat bran, as part of a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease. In addition, low fat diets rich in fiber containing grain products, fruits and vegetables may reduce the risk of some types of cancer, a disease associated with many factors. Organic (per serving): Made with the finest organic grains and sweeteners which were grown without potentially harmful pesticides. Low in Sodium (125 mg): This cereal has 125 mg sodium per serving, and can be part of a low sodium diet that might reduce the risk of developing high blood pressure, which depends on many factors. Low Fat (2.5 g): This cereal is low in fat, containing 2.5 g fat per serving. Recommended daily total fat intake should be less than 35% of total caloric intake. Sugars (8 g): Many cereals are loaded with sugar. For a more healthy diet, it is better to eat cereal with a moderate amount of sugar. Excellent Source of Fiber (5 g): This cereal is an excellent source of fiber. Fiber helps maintain a healthy digestive system. Excellent Source of 6 B Vitamins (20% DV): B vitamins are essential for protein metabolism, production of red blood cells and for the conversion of food into energy. column3: Dairy & casein free. Non GMO. Transfat & cholesterol free. Low in saturated fat. Gluten & wheat free. Low sodium. Certified gluten-free. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Reseal for freshness. We Make People Happy: It all started in the small bakery of a natural foods market on Main Street in Glastonbury, Connecticut. I listened to my celiac customers' concerns about the taste of many of the gluten free options available to them, and thought that no one should have to suffer because of a food allergy or other special dietary need. And so my mission became to create products that would make my customers happy. Today, that mission has expanded to not only make our customers happy with great-tasting gluten free products, but spreading a little bit of happiness to everyone we meet and work with. I'd also like to encourage you to think about the things that make you happy, and to do something to make yourself, a family member, a friend or even a complete stranger happy. Now our bakery is bigger, but we still bake in small batches. We hope you love our products as much as we love creating them for you. Thank you! - Michael Smulders, Founder. column3: Dairy & casein free. Non GMO. Transfat & cholesterol free. Low in saturated fat. Gluten & wheat free. Low sodium. Certified gluten-free. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Reseal for freshness. We Make People Happy: It all started in the small bakery of a natural foods market on Main Street in Glastonbury, Connecticut. I listened to my celiac customers' concerns about the taste of many of the gluten free options available to them, and thought that no one should have to suffer because of a food allergy or other special dietary need. And so my mission became to create products that would make my customers happy. Today, that mission has expanded to not only make our customers happy with great-tasting gluten free products, but spreading a little bit of happiness to everyone we meet and work with. I'd also like to encourage you to think about the things that make you happy, and to do something to make yourself, a family member, a friend or even a complete stranger happy. Now our bakery is bigger, but we still bake in small batches. We hope you love our products as much as we love creating them for you. Thank you! - Michael Smulders, Founder. Our Kashi 7 Whole Grain Pilaf is deliciously hearty, and toasted with just a touch of natural sweetness. Kashi 7 Whole Grain Pilaf is now officially non-GMO project verified. This means it is produced in compliance with the rigorous Non-GMO Project standard. Learn more about GMOs (Genetically Modified Organisms) and work with the non-GMO Project at kashi.com/nongmo. 7 Whole Grains are Better than 1: Just as it's important to have a variety of fruits and vegetables in your diet, it's beneficial to eat a variety of whole grains. That's why we have seven instead of one. After mixing seeds and grains for months, we chose our unique blend known as Kashi Seven Whole Grains & Sesame for the plant protein, fiber and array of vitamins, minerals and phytonutrients not found in most single-grain foods. Whole grains truly are one of nature's superfoods that help you feel your best. Our seven whole grains also provide a variety of colors, textures, shapes and flavors for pure eating enjoyment. With tasty, real food, we believe eating healthy also makes you happy! Learn More About Kashi Seven Whole Grains & Sesame: Buckwheat: hearty in flavor, this seed-like fruit is a good source of fiber. Triticale: natural cross between durum wheat and rye, with higher protein than both. Rye: resilient staple grain with a distinctive earthy flavor. Hard red wheat: hardy grain with a nutty taste often used as bread flour. Barley: smooth, malty flavor and a great source of soluble fiber. Oats: naturally sweet and prized as a great source of soluble fiber. Brown rice: has a delicate flavor and five times the fiber of white rice. Sesame: widely popular and tasty seeds, known for their rich, nutty flavor. We have a whole team of Kashi dedicated to our mission - not just a founder. We're like a family, and we consider you to be part of our extended family. That's why we're sharing our family recipes with you, and invite you to submit your own for a chance to be featured here next time! (Visit us at www.kashi.com/recipe for details). column3: Real. 38% less fat than whole milk. Vitamin A & D. Grade A. UHT. FSC: Mix - Board from responsible sources. www.fsc.org. UHT milk. What is UHT milk? UHT shelf-stable milk is 100% real cow's milk that is ultra pasteurized and packaged in the Tetra Pak container designed to keep the milk pure and safe. The Tetra Pak container protects the milk from any external contamination. This is made possible thanks to its innovative six layered, airtight sealed package. The result is a wholesome milk that can last at room temperature for an extended period of time. Once opened, it has to be refrigerated and consumed within 7 days. Now you know why UHT shelf-stable milk is the best choice for your everyday use at home or away. Just chill and enjoy! UHT shelf-stable milk has advantages, see how they can work for you! Taste: As wholesome as you want milk to be! Wellness: UHT shelf-stable milk contains the essential nutrients our body needs everyday, such as calcium, vitamins, minerals and proteins. The milk box safely maintains all the benefits of milk for your convenience and is the best choice for your everyday use home or away. Fat reduced from 8 g to 5 g per serving. Questions or comments? 1-877-522-8254. Tetra Pak: Protect what's good. Please recycle. RecycleCartons.com. Smart choice! With our special aseptic packaging, UHT shelf-stable milk tastes like real milk because it is real milk! This special packaging process locks out light and air, seals in nutrients and flavor, and allows its contents to remain un-refrigerated for months. For those reasons alone, it's been called the packaging of the future. Tips for On-the-Go Lifestyles: Parents: This product is a convenient, nutritious treat for kids during car trips and airplane flights. Storm Watch: Stock up on our milk products for those unexpected storms that keep you indoors. This is especially useful for the elderly. Travel Tip: Take it with you in the car when you're traveling to a vacation destination. There is no need for refrigeration in transit; just chill when you arrive and enjoy. Run out of milk lately? Keep UHT shelf-stable milk on hand when you don't get to the store often. Store real milk for six months or longer without refrigeration. You'll never reach in the refrigerator for a container of milk past its freshness date again! Flatten box to reduce trash. Sure, So Delicious Dairy Free Coconut Milk tastes great! But what else can this refreshing drink do for you? For decades, we have known about the important role that calcium plays in achieving and maintaining strong bones and helping to prevent osteoporosis. But did you know that magnesium also plays a very important role. Magnesium aids in the body's absorption of calcium and is also instrumental in the strength and formation of bones and teeth. This means that those at risk for osteoporosis can benefit from taking, not only calcium but magnesium as well. So Delicious Dairy Free Coconut Milk is fortified with the proper balance of calcium, magnesium and vitamin D for healthy bones and calcium absorption. Taste, and a healthy lifestyle, all in one. Non GMO Project verified. 60% MCFAs: The body needs a variety of fats for healthy cell function. Consumption of good fats is an important part of a balanced diet. The fat in coconut milk contains approximately 60% medium chain fatty acids (MCFAs). Amongst a number of unique properties associated with MCFAs is the fact that they are not readily stored but rather used as energy in the body. 4 g saturated fat (Comprised of about 60% medium chain fatty acids (MCFAs)). column1: Native Forest Coconut Milk Powder
column3: Make a great creamer! Instant! Just add water. Dairy free. Vegan. Gluten free. A staple of traditional Asian and Caribbean cuisines, coconut milk lends its rich and creamy goodness to many wonderful regional dishes. Now you can enjoy coconut milk in a convenient non-dairy powder that requires no refrigeration. It's an excellent choice for the home chef who values the convenience of a powdered milk, but wants to avoid the dairy and the additives that often accompany it. To produce Native Forest Coconut Milk Powder, we spray-dry fresh coconut milk, adding only select, plant-based ingredients (less than 3 percent tapioca maltodextrin and less than one half of one percent sugar esters) to protect, disperse and balance nutrients when the milk becomes powder. There are no other ingredients. Convenient and easy to use, Native Forest Coconut Milk Powder is great to take camping or traveling since it has no need of refrigeration. It dissolves quickly when stirred in hot water and may soon become your favorite ingredient in soups, curries, sauces, desserts and beverages. Native Forest Coconut Milk Powder is part of the Edward & Sons family of products, offering convenience without compromise since 1978. Our policy prohibits the use of genetically engineered ingredients. See www.edwardandsonsrecipes.org for delicious recipes using coconut milk powder and all of our products. www.edwardandsons.com. Indulge by the glass, use it in baking, or make a smoothie by blending it with frozen fruit. These are the good fats that help maintain a healthy heart, a sharp mind, a strong immune system, and glowing skin. Nature's most perfect food. column1: Soy Slender Soymilk, Vanilla
column3: No sugar added. Soy protein. Reduced calorie. 45% fewer calories than the leading soymilk brands. Low fat. Dairy/lactose free. 1 g net carbs. The Soy Slender essentials: no sugar added; 1 g net carbs (1 g net carbs equals total carbohydrates less dietary fiber); 6.25 grams of soy protein; 33 mg isoflavones; low fat, reduced calorie; made from whole soybeans, no soy protein isolates; excellent source of calcium, vitamin D and riboflavin; a cholesterol free food; lactose and dairy free. Soy Slender and your health. Did you know that heart disease is the leading cause of death among US adults (National Center for Health Statistics 2000)? Diets low in saturated fat and cholesterol that include 25 grams of soy protein a day may reduce the risk of heart disease. One serving of Soy Slender provides 6.25 g of soy protein. Easy pour, reclosable spout! What's so special about Soy Slender? Soy Slender brings you the benefits of soymilk wrapped in a delicious vanilla flavor without any sugar added. Because it's sweetened with sucralose (Splenda Brand), you can enjoy a creamy, chilled glassful knowing that you've cut your calories and your carbs! What you haven't cut is nutrition - each serving of Soy Slender has 6.25 grams of soy protein, 33 mg of isoflavones, no cholesterol, and is low in fat. You need your calcium! Our Family Story: Our family is passionate about making great-tasting coffee. In 1919, my great-grandfather Cap Saurage discovered the secret of making our special coffee. He named it Community Coffee out of appreciation for his community of friends and the customers he served. Four generations later, our family is still active in selecting, roasting and perfecting great-tasting blends for coffee lovers everywhere. Our store continues at communitycoffee.com. Breakfast Blend: This aromatic, medium roast is sure to awaken your senses and follow with a smooth and bright finish. Made from only the top 10% of the world's coffee beans. Taste the Difference: We focus on every detail of our coffee so that each package is consistently fresh and flavorful. It's a tradition our family embraced decades ago, and it's just as important to our process today. We work with many family-run farms, and the relationships we've built over the years are essential to the quality and taste of our coffees. Using recipes perfected over four generations, we roast and blend these coffees to create the rich, smooth flavor you've come to expect time after time, cup after cup. column1: Don Franciscos Coffee, Gourmet, All Purpose Grind, Medium Roast, Hawaiian Hazelnut
column3: Since 1870. The flavor of plump hazelnuts complements this blend of exotic coffees to bring you an enchanting cup. Four generations of master roasting. Don Francisco. Each coffee-growing country offers many grades of coffee, some excellent and some not. But a country's reputation is always built on its very best grade. Many brands mix poor-quality coffee beans with good ones to keep costs down. That's why a coffee lover can be so pleased with one cup, and so disappointed with another. We never mix the quality of coffee. We choose the very highest grade of beans from the best coffee-growing countries, and we keep them pure. Then we roast them in a way that brings out their unique flavor, just the way my family has for over 135 years. So if you want coffee that's built the reputation, it's inside. We hope each country's best will give you the pleasure only a great cup of coffee can. - Don Francisco. Sustainability: Don Francisco taught us to respect and honor the land and its people. That principle is in every aspect of our business today. We are committed to improving the way our coffee-growing partners care for their land, and to enriching their communities through education and healthcare programs. Lively Flavors: Don Francisco's has discovered a way to balance the taste of freshly-roasted coffee with the bouquet of lively flavorings. You'll discover that the appetizing aromas of roasted nuts, zesty cinnamon, butterscotch, or creamy vanilla will bring your coffee experience to new heights of satisfaction. 100% Arabica: Of the two main varieties of coffee, Arabica beans brew a more aromatic and flavorful beverage. The great coffees of the world, such as Colombian and Kona, are Arabicas. These more-flavorful beans appear in stores as whole bean, and in high-quality ground coffees. Blend Adventure: We followed the aroma of coffee from our original shops to far-off destinations across the world. Each stop taught us something new about coffee - and more importantly, about ourselves. Exploring has led to incredible discoveries about how to brew and who we are. column3: The sweet zest of cinnamon sticks and smooth aroma of hazelnuts bring you a most satisfying cup. Four generations of master roasting. Since 1870. Each coffee-growing country offers many grades of coffee, some excellent and some not. But a country's reputation is always built on its very best grade. Many brands mix poor-quality coffee beans with good ones to keep costs down. That's why a coffee lover can be so pleased with one cup, and so disappointed with another. We never mix the quality of coffee. We choose the very highest grade of beans from the best coffee-growing countries, and we keep them pure. Then we roast them in a way that brings out their unique flavor, just the way my family has for over 135 years. So if you want coffee that's built the reputation, it's inside. We hope each country's best will give you the pleasure only a great cup of coffee can. - Don Francisco. Sustainability: Don Francisco taught us to respect and honor the land and its people. That principle is in every aspect of our business today. We are committed to improving the way our coffee-growing partners care for their land, and to enriching their communities through education and healthcare programs. column1: Publix Premium Coffee, Ground, Breakfast Blend
column3: Publix Premium Breakfast Blend Coffee brews up bright with a nutty flavor for an easy-drinking cup that's the perfect start to your day. Discover all our varieties. publix.com. It could be said that a delicious cup of coffee is an exquisite combination of science and art. Myriad components play a part in the creation of great-tasting coffee, from the geography and climate of its cultivation, to the artistry and skill of blending and brewing it. The two most critical are the beans and the roast. The Arabica coffee beans we use are the world's finest, grown only at certain elevations between the Tropic of Cancer and the Tropic of Capricorn. Relatively delicate plants, they require expert nurturing to flourish and produce the delicate fruit that contains the coffee bean. Careful roasting gives coffee its rich, delicious flavor. During the process, which takes only minutes, natural sugars within the coffee beans are released and become caramelized on the beans' surface. The longer the roast, the fuller the flavor of (and, somewhat surprisingly, the less caffeine in) the coffee. You can rejoice in the taste of Publix Premium Ground Coffee, because our Arabica beans have been roasted to perfection. Whichever blend you choose, we guarantee you'll enjoy its marvelous taste cup after cup. Publix Guarantee: We will never knowingly disappoint you. column3: Publix Premium Colombian Coffee brews up rich and lively with subtle fruity notes for a profound coffee experience. Discover all our varieties. publix.com. It could be said that a delicious cup of coffee is an exquisite combination of science and art. Myriad components play a part in the creation of great-tasting coffee, from the geography and climate of its cultivation, to the artistry and skill of blending and brewing it. The two most critical are the beans and the roast. The Arabica coffee beans we use are the world's finest, grown only at certain elevations between the Tropic of Cancer and the Tropic of Capricorn. Relatively delicate plants, they require expert nurturing to flourish and produce the delicate fruit that contains the coffee bean. Careful roasting gives coffee its rich, delicious flavor. During the process, which takes only minutes, natural sugars within the coffee beans are released and become caramelized on the beans' surface. The longer the roast, the fuller the flavor of (and, somewhat surprisingly, the less caffeine in) the coffee. You can rejoice in the taste of Publix Premium Ground Coffee, because our Arabica beans have been roasted to perfection. Whichever blend you choose, we guarantee you'll enjoy its marvelous taste cup after cup. Publix Guarantee: We will never knowingly disappoint you. column1: Don Franciscos Coffee, Gourmet, All Purpose Grind, Medium, Hawaiian Blend
column3: Since 1870. Kona, Kauai, Molokai, or Maui are blended with Central America's richest coffees to create a distinctive cup. All-purpose grind. Don Francisco. Each coffee-growing country offers many grades of coffee, some excellent and some not. But a country's reputation is always built on its very best grade. Many brands mix poor-quality coffee beans with good ones to keep costs down. That's why a coffee lover can be so pleased with one cup, and so disappointed with another. We never mix the quality of coffee. We choose the very highest grade of beans from the best coffee-growing countries, and we keep them pure. Then we roast them in a way that brings out their unique flavor, just the way my family has for over 135 years. So if you want coffee that's built the reputation, it's inside. We hope each country's best will give you the pleasure only a great cup of coffee can. - Don Francisco. Sustainability: Don Francisco taught us to respect and honor the land and its people. That principle is in every aspect of our business today. We are committed to improving the way our coffee-growing partners care for their land, and to enriching their communities through education and healthcare programs. Volcanic Soil: These coffees are born in rich, volcanic soils, raised in special micro-climates. Branch-ripened and hand-picked. These selections are the best of their regions, and roasted to deliver their unique flavor treasures. One of our most popular and satisfying blends. 100% Arabica: Of the two main varieties of coffee, Arabica beans brew a more aromatic and flavorful beverage. The great coffees of the world, such as Colombian and Kona, are Arabicas. These more-flavorful beans appear in stores as whole bean, and in high-quality ground coffees. column3: For my wife, this blend of grace, full of aroma and good taste. You'll love its smoothness, it's never bitter. So relax with a cup, leave the kids with a sitter. Blend. USDA organic. Certified B corporation. Patience. From farm. To roast. To brew. The coffee you hold in your hand today is a product of patience. The patience of an organic coffee farmer growing the most complex, flavorful beans. Of a team taking the time to meticulously source and roast each batch to hit the exact flavor notes. And finally, the patience you show in brewing a cup of coffee best described as yours. We call it coffee with character. And we hope you love it as much as we do. Please satisfy your curiosity by visiting us on our website or on social media. We have lots of good stuff there. JimsOrganicCoffee.com. Certified organic by Oregon Tilth. Jim's Notes - We all love coffee. Its tantalizing aroma, how it brings a smile to our face, how it slows down our busy world. We've seen firsthand the benefits of organic. From the inspiring farmers and their lush, biodiverse ecosystems to our cupping table where we select only the finest coffees. We take great pride in providing consistently amazing coffee and are truly grateful to be a small organic part of one's daily routine. Now we make our delicious drinking chocolates using only Rainforest Alliance Certified cacao. Rainforest Alliance certified farms support a healthy environment, promote the well-being of workers and their communities and ensure efficient farm methods. Farm workers benefit from safe working conditions, enjoy dignified housing and medical care, and access to schools for their children. Certification ensures the protection of ecosystems, including wildlife habitat, water and soil. To learn more about the Rainforest Alliance, visit www.rainforest-alliance.org.
